## Basic processing pipeline

```text
1. Collect images
   - own photos
   - 360° panoramas
   - optional external street-level imagery

2. Read metadata
   - GPS position
   - timestamp
   - heading / azimuth if available
   - camera type
   - image ID

3. Run semantic segmentation
   - classify pixels into available model classes
   - calculate class percentages

4. Store per-image results
   - CSV
   - GeoJSON
   - GeoPackage
   - optional mask images

5. Aggregate spatially
   - by street segment
   - by point clusters
   - by grid / hexagons
   - by route
   - by neighborhood / area

6. Visualize
   - QGIS maps
   - heatmaps
   - street segment styling
   - HTML reports
```

