## Possible semantic classes

With common urban semantic segmentation models, useful classes may include:

```text
road
sidewalk
building
wall
fence
pole
traffic light
traffic sign
vegetation
terrain
sky
person
rider
car
truck
bus
train
motorcycle
bicycle
```

Most valuable classes for GIS-style analysis:

```text
vegetation
road
sidewalk
building
terrain
sky
car / vehicle classes
person / rider / bicycle
```

Important limitation:

There may be no reliable `water` class in common Cityscapes-style pretrained models.

Water may be misclassified as:

```text
road
terrain
sky
vegetation
```

depending on appearance, reflection and context.

For water, nature-specific classes, snow, wetlands, fields, tree species or ecological detail, a better model or custom training would be needed.

