## Risks and limitations

Important limitations:

- semantic segmentation classes may not match local GIS/nature needs,
- water may not be reliable,
- seasonal effects can strongly influence vegetation visibility,
- weather and lighting matter,
- camera height matters,
- car-based photos and pedestrian photos produce different perception,
- 360° stitching artifacts may influence segmentation,
- privacy and faces/license plate handling may be needed,
- third-party imagery licenses must be checked,
- interpolation must be described as perceived visual index, not objective land cover.

---

## Privacy and ethics

Street-level imagery may contain:

- faces,
- license plates,
- private properties,
- people,
- sensitive locations.

For a public repository:

- do not include real street-level imagery unless license and privacy are clear,
- use synthetic or heavily anonymized samples,
- avoid publishing exact sensitive locations if not needed,
- document limitations and privacy handling.

