## Strategic value

This could become one of the most original CVC/GIS ideas.

Reason:

```text
Many tools detect objects.
Fewer tools map how people visually experience space using geotagged semantic segmentation.
```

The strongest angle:

```text
Computer vision + GIS + perceived landscape / urban experience
```

This is close to Green View Index thinking, but could be adapted to local data, own 360° camera imagery and QGIS workflows.

---

## Short summary

CVC StreetView GIS would process many geotagged street-level images or 360° panoramas, calculate semantic class percentages for each image or direction sector, and turn those values into GIS layers and maps.

It would help answer:

```text
How green does this street feel?
How dominant are roads and hard surfaces?
How enclosed is the street by buildings?
How much sky is visible?
How does the city look from a human perspective?
```

This is not classic object counting. It is visual landscape analysis from street-level imagery.

The 360° camera makes the concept much stronger, because it reduces direction bias and allows full-view or sector-based analysis around each observation point.
